{% extends 'Actor/main.jinja2' %}

{%- block instructions %}
Does the user's query need clarification before a planning agent can act on it?

Most queries have an obvious default interpretation — prefer answering yes=false.
Only answer yes=true when ALL of these hold:
- Multiple interpretations would lead to fundamentally different actions (not just different parameter values)
- No single interpretation is clearly what most users would mean
- The ambiguity cannot be resolved by the downstream system from the data itself
